@startuml diagram
title Platform for Selecting Best Embedding Model - Architecture Overview
top to bottom direction

package "User-Facing Layer" {
  [Web Frontend\n(Azure App Service)] as Frontend
  [Backend API\n(Azure App Service)] as Backend
  [User Authentication\n(Azure AD B2C / Entra ID)] as Auth
}

package "Compute & AI" {
  [Azure Functions\n(Benchmark Workers)] as Functions
  [Azure OpenAI\n(LLM-as-judge,\noptional embeddings)] as OpenAI
}

package "Data & Storage" {
  database "Azure Cosmos DB\n(users, experiments,\nmodel metadata, results)" as Cosmos
  database "Azure Blob Storage\n(raw uploaded data)" as Blob
}

Frontend -down-> Backend : User requests\n(upload, run benchmark)
Backend -right-> Auth : Login / auth checks

Backend -down-> Functions : Trigger benchmark
Functions -right-> OpenAI : LLM-as-judge\nrelevance scoring

Backend -down-> Cosmos : Store/read\nexperiment metadata
Functions -down-> Cosmos : Store benchmark\nresults

Backend -down-> Blob : Upload user data
Functions -down-> Blob : Read input data

@enduml
